One of the biggest barriers to cooking frequently is that it takes practice and time to gain proficiency and ease.
That initial training time has simply not been available to most Americans, as the pace of life has intensified over the decades.
An increase in the frequency of cooking does not necessarily mean we are getting healthier during the pandemic.
Tragedy and fear are making us stress-eat, as we drown ourselves in tubs of ice cream or binge bake.
A number of medical schools, such as George Washington University and Tulane University, now have culinary schools or culinary programs.